{"lemma":"خِنْزِيراتٌ","slug":"خِنْزِيراتٌ","root":"خ.ن.ز.ر","root_slug":"خ-ن-ز-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ن-ز-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خِنْزِير","root":"خنزر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10495"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%90%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pig, swine, hog","examples":[{"text":"حُرِّمَتْ عَلَيْكُمُ ٱلْمَيْتَةُ وَٱلدَّمُ وَلَحْمُ ٱلْخِنزِيرِ[…]","english":"Forbidden to you are carrion, blood, and pork […]"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pig, despicable, disgusting person","tags":["derogatory"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"porky, pig, state henchman","tags":["derogatory"],"examples":[{"text":"وفي الليالي إذ كنا نجوع كان حسين يتسلل الى غرفتهم بخفة القط ويسرق مختلف الأطعمة الشهية. معلبات وحليب وجبنة وفواكه كنا نوزعها على فقراء المعتقل الآخرين، قائلين:\n ―كلوا، إنها من غرفة الخنازير.","english":"In nights when we were hungry Hussayn sneaked into their room in cat’s stealth and stole diverse desirable foodstuff. Canned food and milk and cheese and fruits we shared amongst the other poor inmates, saying:\nEat, it’s from the pig’s room."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"An old borrowing of Aramaic חֲזִירָא (ḥăzīrā) / ܚܙܺܝܪܳܐ (ḥəzīrā), akin to Hebrew חֲזִיר (ḥăzīr) and Ugaritic 𐎃𐎐𐎇𐎗 (ḫnzr), and Akkadian 𒄷𒍣𒊏 (ḫuzīru), a rare borrowing particular to Old Assyrian."},"ipa":["/xin.ziːr/","/χənˈziːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10495","headword_ar":"خِنْزِيرٌ","root":"xzr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hog;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pig;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain foul animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be forbidden"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be eaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by every prophet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanaAziyru","text_ar":"خَنَازِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) not, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzorN","text_ar":"خُزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [though this is an epithet applicable to swine:] (TA:) accord. to some, it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEoliylN","text_ar":"فِعْلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not [generally] added as a second letter: but accord. to others, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"finoEiylN","text_ar":"فِنْعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes added as a second letter, and because it is held to be derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazira","text_ar":"خَزِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", since all"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xnAzyr","text_ar":"خنازير"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzor","text_ar":"خُزْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as it is said in the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u xinoziyrK A^axozaru","text_ar":"كُلُّ خِنْزِيرٍ اَخْزَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanaAziyru","text_ar":"خَنَازِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrofula;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glandular swellings in the neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ulcers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard ulcers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which arise in the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ganglions, or hard or nodous lumps beneath the skin, in the neck, and in soft parts, such as the armpits; but most frequently in the neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","TA"]}]}}